# ============================================
# Image Generation Configuration
# ============================================

# Select which AI provider to use for image generation
# Options: OPENAI | GEMINI | LEAP
# Default: OPENAI (if not specified)
IMAGE_REPOSITORY_TYPE=OPENAI

# ============================================
# Provider API Keys (required)
# ============================================

# OpenAI API Key (for DALL-E 3)
# Get it from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-...

# Gemini API Key (for Imagen 3)
# Get it from: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=...

# Leap API Key (legacy - optional)
# Get it from: https://tryleap.ai/
LEAP_API_KEY=...

# ============================================
# Provider Selection Guide
# ============================================

# Use OPENAI (DALL-E 3) when:
# - You need complex prompt understanding
# - You want automatic prompt enhancement (GPT-4 rewriting)
# - You need HD quality images
# - You prefer vivid/natural styles
# Cost: ~$0.04/image (standard), ~$0.08/image (HD)

# Use GEMINI (Imagen 3) when:
# - You need photorealistic images
# - You want artistic styles (impressionism, anime, etc.)
# - You need multiple images per request
# - You want the lowest cost option
# Cost: ~$0.03/image
# ⚠️ REQUIRES: Google Cloud billing enabled
# Error if not enabled: "Imagen API is only accessible to billed users"

# Use LEAP when:
# - You have an existing Leap API subscription
# - You need their specific model capabilities
# Cost: Varies by plan

# ============================================
# Quick Setup Instructions
# ============================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.images.example .env

# 2. Add your API keys above

# 3. Choose your provider (IMAGE_REPOSITORY_TYPE)

# 4. Test with Slack:
#    Send message: "img a beautiful sunset"

# 5. Check response includes provider info:
#    "Imágenes generadas con openai:"

# ============================================
# Advanced Configuration
# ============================================

# To switch providers programmatically (optional):
# See: src/app.ts or ImagesServices.getInstance(ImageRepositoryType.GEMINI)

# To use different providers for different users/channels:
# Extend ImagesServices to accept repositoryType parameter
# and pass it from the controller based on user preference
